This paper deals with the anonymization of social graphs, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the paper specifically focuses on social network datasets. The second likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as the paper discusses the privacy guarantees provided by graph anonymization mechanisms and proposes a method to mitigate vulnerabilities. The third likely category is cs.DB (Databases), as the paper deals with the anonymization of graph data. The fourth likely category is cs.SD (Software Engineering), as the paper proposes a method to enhance existing anonymization mechanisms. The fifth likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper proposes a metric based on graph embedding and relies on a Gaussian mixture model for edge plausibility thresholding.
